# Email Configuration (SMTP)

# Gmail SMTP
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
FROM_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# Alternative SMTP (uncomment and configure)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.your-provider.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USER=your-username
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-password
# FROM_EMAIL=sender@your-domain.com

# AI email-drafting persona
# A free-form description of WHO is sending the cold emails. The drafting
# prompt injects this verbatim so the model can write like you instead of
# falling back to vague "we supply premium / reliable / competition-grade"
# filler. Without it, drafts will be honest about uncertainty rather than
# fabricating credentials, but they'll be noticeably weaker. Multi-line is
# fine — wrap in single quotes if you use newlines via an env loader that
# supports them.
#
# Include things like:
#   - your business / your name and one line on what makes you distinct
#   - rough price point or pricing range you can quote
#   - specific deliverables you offer (samples, data, intros, ride-alongs)
#   - one or two named references or recognizable customers (only if true)
#   - the voice you want — terse / warm / dry / nerdy
#
# Example (single-line):
# EMAIL_SENDER_PROFILE="Mark at Bay Brisket Co. — wholesale packer briskets, $5.20–$5.80/lb delivered Bay Area, free 10lb sample on request, currently supplying [named customer]. Voice: terse, no fluff."
